# =============================================================================
# Bigfoot Trailers — workspace root gitignore
#
# Strategy: whitelist. Ignore EVERYTHING at the root by default, then
# explicitly allow only the two project folders we want on GitHub.
# This guarantees no stray .env, log, docx, pptx, node_modules, .claude
# folder, or other workspace clutter ever ends up in version control.
# =============================================================================

# Step 1 — ignore every entry at the repo root.
/*

# Step 2 — explicitly allow what we want.
!/.gitignore
!/.gitattributes
!/bigfoot-api
!/bigfoot_mobile

# Note: each subproject ships its own .gitignore for its internals
# (node_modules, build outputs, .env files, secrets, etc.).
